race.comment: KING JERRY (12) deep into his prep and looks up to this stiffer contest with McEvoy taking the reins. Slashing effort two-back in this company, before being collared late with the 57.5kg over this trip at Scone. Brings the right figures to take this out. SOUTHERN DANCER (8) versatile Wagga-trained mare who deserves her shot in town. Stalked the speed when up in trip for a gritty victory over 1675m at Wagga Riverside. Racing in career best form and doesn't have to improve much to take this out. WANDJAD (13) strong late from back in the field at his second run in when eighth over 1500m at Rosehill in this company. Blinkers come off and has each way claims. UPWARDLY MOBILE (9) consistent mare who returned solid figures again from back in the pack when fifth over 1500m at Rosehill in this class. Ready for the mile and no shock to see her win this. CHRISTA (1) due for a change of luck after finishing in the minor money at her last four starts. Fitter now. The chances don't end there.
